5.2 to 7.1 MJ of electricity per kg of cement through electrolyzer. 6.15gj per tonne is the mean.  Little to no supplemental heat required. Source: Ellis, L. D., Badel, A. F., Chiang, M. L., Park, R. J. Y., & Chiang, Y. M. (2020). Toward electrochemical synthesis of cement—An electrolyzer-based process for decarbonating CaCO3 while producing useful gas streams. Proceedings of the National Academy of Sciences, 117(23), 12584-12591.
